ODE XII.

AElius Lamias, to whom this ode was addressed, was a. ¹person of illustrious family and considerable estate. He had risen by his personal merit to the rank of lieutenant-general in the Spanish war under Augustus. He so demeaned himself in this office as to gain the esteem and respect of the army. Horace therefore com- pliments him on the hereditary honors, which he so well sustain- ed 3 and upon which his own character and achievements had shed additional lustre. And since he predicts a storm on the morrow, he invites Lamias to pass the day with him.
